      <header id="article-head">
        <div class="title entry-title">
            <h1 class="page-title">getUTCDay</h1>
                        

            
            
                                </div>
        

        
               </header>

           
                                  
            
      <div id="wikiArticle" class="page-content boxed">
                
                                <p>Â </p>
<h3 id="Summary" name="Summary">Summary</h3>
<p>Returns the day of the week in the specified date according to universal time, where 0 represents Sunday.</p>
<table class="standard-table">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th class="header" colspan="2">Method of <a href="/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Date"><code>Date</code></a></th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Implemented in</td>
      <td>JavaScript 1.3</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>ECMAScript Edition</td>
      <td>ECMAScript 1st Edition</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<h3 id="Syntax" name="Syntax">Syntax</h3>
<p><code>getUTCDay() </code></p>
<h3 id="Parameters" name="Parameters">Parameters</h3>
<p>None.</p>
<h3 id="Description" name="Description">Description</h3>
<p>The value returned by <code>getUTCDay</code> is an integer corresponding to the day of the week: 0 for Sunday, 1 for Monday, 2 for Tuesday, and so on.</p>
<h3 id="Examples" name="Examples">Examples</h3>
<h4 id="Example:_Using_getUTCDay" name="Example:_Using_getUTCDay">Example: Using <code>getUTCDay</code></h4>
<p>The following example assigns the weekday portion of the current date to the variable <code>weekday</code>.</p>
<pre>var weekday;
Today = new Date()
weekday = Today.getUTCDay()
</pre>
